inline_comments.message:
@Sylvain, our goal is to create certs for client and server during OOM make all command, as described in https://jira.onap.org/browse/AAF-1084 
But because we are doing this in agile and are very close to RC0 we decided that first we will implement HTTPS support in both client and server to finalize Java implementation - see https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/aaf/certservice/+/103678, provide in OOM installation predefined certificates (this PR) and in new PR add to OOM procedure to generate certificates very similar to https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/aaf/certservice/+/103678/23/certs/Makefile 

I won't close AAF-1084 without automatic certificates generation in OOM for CertService client and server. IF this doesn't convince you to accept this PR, you can create a BUG that certs are hardcoded and assign it to me.
